          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "When you call either ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coregraphics/cgevent/1454426-tapcreate",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " or ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coregraphics/cgevent/1454828-tapcreateforpsn",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " to register an event tap, you supply a bit mask that identifies the set of events to be observed. You specify each event using one of the event type constants listed in ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coregraphics/cgeventtype",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ". To form the bit mask, use the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "CGEventMaskBit",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " macro to convert each constant into an event mask and then OR the individual masks together. For example:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "CGEventMask mask = CGEventMaskBit(kCGEventLeftMouseDown) |",
            "                   CGEventMaskBit(kCGEventLeftMouseUp);"
          ],
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "1967890",
            "title": "Listing 1"
          },
          "syntax": "occ",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You can also supply a mask to observe all events:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "CGEventMask mask = kCGEventMaskForAllEvents;"
          ],
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "1967896",
            "title": "Listing 2"
          },
          "syntax": "occ",
          "type": "codeListing"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
